Requires OCaml (>= 4.01), Zarith (Debian package libzarith-ocaml-dev),
Camlp4 (optional but highly recommended, Debian package camlp4), CSDP
(no Debian package), MOSEK (no Debian package, optional),
SDPA{,-GMP,-DD} (optional) and Ocaml-glpk (no Debian package,
optional).

To install Csdp:
* install dependencies:
  * libatlas-base-dev
  * libatlas-dev
  * libblas-dev
  * gfortran
* download it from https://projects.coin-or.org/Csdp/
  http://www.coin-or.org/download/source/Csdp/Csdp-6.1.1.tgz
* Apply our patchs (modified install target and enable the use of global
  param.csdp)
  tar xvzf Csdp-6.1.1.tgz
  cd Csdp-6.1.1
  for i in path_to_osdp/external/csdp_*.patch; do patch -p0 < $i; done
* type make, sudo make install

If you use MOSEK: Don't forget to set both PATH *and* LD_LIBRARY_PATH
to the directory containing the mosek binaries and libraries.

If you use SDPA-GMP: apply the patch external/sdpa_gmp.patch
before compiling SDPA-GMP.

If you use SDPA-DD: install the QD library from
http://crd-legacy.lbl.gov/~dhbailey/mpdist before compiling SDPA-DD.

Configure:
% ./configure

Compile:
% make

Install:
# make install

# make install-deps  # Optionnal, to make Csdp less verbose
